{PARA 241 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 40 "Hopf bifurcation at d=0.2955 in y and z
." }{TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 237 "" 0 "" {TEXT 212 0 "" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 
237 "" 0 "" {TEXT 212 0 "" }}{PARA 242 "" 0 "" {TEXT 211 29 "e. Dissip
ative system or not?" }{TEXT 211 0 "" }}{PARA 237 "" 0 "" {TEXT 212 0 
"" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 237 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 237 "" 0 "" 
{TEXT 212 104 " The divergence of the system is considered as an appro
priate measure of the system's \"dissipativeness\"." }{TEXT 212 0 "" }
}{PARA 243 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 237 "" 0 "" {TEXT 212 42 "Cre
ate function for divergence operator..." }{TEXT 212 0 "" }}{PARA 237 "
" 0 "" {TEXT 212 0 "" }}{PARA 235 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 54 "diff(f1(x
,y,z),x)+diff(f2(x,y,z),y)+diff(f3(x,y,z),z);" }{MPLTEXT 1 0 0 "" }}
{PARA 235 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 29 "dvg := unapply(%, (x, y, z));" }
{MPLTEXT 1 0 0 "" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 235 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 22 "d := \+
0.5; tend := 500;" }{MPLTEXT 1 0 0 "" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 235 "> " 0 "" 
{MPLTEXT 1 0 71 "sol := dsolve(\{sys, ic\}, type=numeric, maxfun=-1,ou
tput=listprocedure);" }{MPLTEXT 1 0 0 "" }}{PARA 235 "> " 0 "" 
{MPLTEXT 1 0 122 "odeplot(sol, [t, dvg(x(t), y(t), z(t))], tend/2..ten
d, labels=[\"t\",\"Nabla f\"], numpoints=tend*100,color=blue,axes=norm
al);" }{MPLTEXT 1 0 0 "" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 237 "" 0 "" {TEXT 212 0 "" }}
{PARA 237 "" 0 "" {TEXT 212 728 "A system is called dissipative when i
nfinitesimal volumes in phase-space shrink in time. Loosely speaking o
ne could say that a dissipative system forgets its roots, and all poin
ts are in some way attracted to a point, limit cycle, or strange attra
ctor. As can be seen from the equation of divergence, this system is n
ot dissipative everywhere in the domain, as it contains the variables \+
x,y and z. However, when we study the time-evolution of the divergence
, it can be seen that the system is strongly dissipative most of the t
ime, except at very short time intervals that are connected to the rel
axation oscillations. So time-averaged, the system is dissipative, wit
h the volume shrinking characteristically as V ~ exp(-330*t)." }{TEXT 
212 0 "" }{TEXT 212 1 "\n" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 235 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 
0 "" }}}{PARA 244 "" 0 "" {TEXT 210 0 "" }}{PARA 245 "" 0 "" {TEXT 
